Question: What is likely to have a better school cafeteria?
Options: A. high school B. canteen C. polytechnic D. large room E. all kinds of schools

C. polytechnic

Polytechnic schools, which often focus on technical and vocational education, tend to have better-funded facilities including school cafeterias compared to high schools or canteens in general educational institutions. These institutions may prioritize providing quality amenities to support the overall student experience and well-being.
